translate ru strings:

    old "Do not listen to her!"
    new "Do not listen to her!"

    old "Seize Marion Achillea immediately!"
    new "Seize Marion Achillea immediately!"

    old "For a moment, there was confusion on the room, the soldiers unsure of whom to listen to."
    new "For a moment, there was confusion on the room, the soldiers unsure of whom to listen to."

    old "I am the king, and I order you to seize him!"
    new "I am the king, and I order you to seize him!"

    old "This reminder was enough for the soldiers, and they moved again, grabbing Marion, wrestling him to the ground as he tried to fight them."
    new "This reminder was enough for the soldiers, and they moved again, grabbing Marion, wrestling him to the ground as he tried to fight them."

    old "You promised! Is your word worth nothing!?"
    new "You promised! Is your word worth nothing!?"

    old "Marion's voice broke as he screamed. One of the soldiers cracked him across the mouth with his mailed fist."
    new "Marion's voice broke as he screamed. One of the soldiers cracked him across the mouth with his mailed fist."

    old "Blood and teeth splattered across the floor, and Marion slumped over. Either unconscious or too stunned to speak."
    new "Blood and teeth splattered across the floor, and Marion slumped over. Either unconscious or too stunned to speak."

    old "The soldiers began to drag him away."
    new "The soldiers began to drag him away."

    old "Thomas. I gave him my word he would be safe."
    new "Thomas. I gave him my word he would be safe."

    old "And you were smart to lie to him like that, but I won't allow him to escape for what he did."
    new "And you were smart to lie to him like that, but I won't allow him to escape for what he did."

    old "He tried to destroy our country, kill me, and if he had won, he would have killed you too."
    new "He tried to destroy our country, kill me, and if he had won, he would have killed you too."

    old "If we let him live in exile, it won't be long until he's back."
    new "If we let him live in exile, it won't be long until he's back."

    old "Unlike father, I'm not going to let these problems fester. We rip the traitors out by the root, starting with Marion, the one who caused all of this."
    new "Unlike father, I'm not going to let these problems fester. We rip the traitors out by the root, starting with Marion, the one who caused all of this."

    old "Sarah wanted to keep her word to Marion, but Thomas was right. He was the king, and his order stood over hers. There was nothing she could do."
    new "Sarah wanted to keep her word to Marion, but Thomas was right. He was the king, and his order stood over hers. There was nothing she could do."

    old "Still, it did not trouble Sarah that much."
    new "Still, it did not trouble Sarah that much."

    old "Her brother had been right. Marion would have killed her without thinking anything of it."
    new "Her brother had been right. Marion would have killed her without thinking anything of it."

    old "Whatever punishment was coming for him was entirely earned."
    new "Whatever punishment was coming for him was entirely earned."

    old "For now, this is where the game ends."
    new "For now, this is where the game ends."

